            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;This is better than the accepted answer in that it gives more control over the delimiter, prefix and suffix. However, I would remove superfluous &lt;code&gt;toString()&lt;/code&gt; in the final &lt;code&gt;System.out.println()&lt;/code&gt; and used it in &lt;code&gt;joiner.add(element.toString())&lt;/code&gt; instead of adding the empty string. This solution works for arrays of non-primitive types as well, uniformly.&lt;/span&gt;

